  <content>= Table of Content =

{{toc /}}

= Introduction =

This macro displays a Microsoft 365 document using the Microsoft 365 platform. To use this macro you need to configure the Microsoft365 accesses in the administration.

This macro can be used either to embed by URL or by searching the document in Microsoft 365 and storing the associated data in the document.

The viewer uses the Microsoft 365 viewer for office documents. For PDFs we cannot use the Microsoft 365 viewer because of a limitation on Microsoft 365 which does not allow to embed their viewer for PDFs. We use the XWiki PDF Viewer if it is installed in XWiki, otherwise we do not display anything.

= Macro Syntax =

{{code}}
This is the syntax to search document in Microsoft 365. You will be shown a search box to search for a document. You can select which document to embed.

{{microsoft365 /}}

This is the syntax to embed by URL. You just need to copy paste the URL that is in your browser bar when you are viewing or editing a Microsoft 365 document:
{{/code}}

= Limitations =

Embedding by URL cannot work for PDF documents. However PDF documents can be embedded by searching them and requires the PDF Viewer macro installed in the Wiki.

= Examples =

{{velocity}}
#if($request.showexamples||$request.update||$request.nb)
== Embed via Search Example ==

{{microsoft365 /}}

== Embed via URL Example ==

This examples uses an XWiki URL. The document might not be allowed to view without a Microsoft 365 account.

{{microsoft365 url="https://xwikidev-my.sharepoint.com/personal/microsoft365_xwikidev_onmicrosoft_com/_layouts/15/WopiFrame.aspx?sourcedoc=%7BD5A1847B-742D-42EB-980F-4964A21E4F05%7D&amp;file=XWikiKeyMessages2017.pptx&amp;action=default" /}}
#else
[[Show examples&gt;&gt;||queryString="showexamples=1"]]
#end
{{/velocity}}</content>
